CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 26, 1953, pg. 1, reads: "SCHENLEY 'INSPIRATIONS' - Schenley High gridders will have oodles of beauty to inspire them in their gridiron battles this season. In addition to these beauties who act as cheerleaders at the games, the school has a majorette corps.  Putting their all into a call to 'fight for dear old Schenley' are...Top row, left to right, are: Maxine Cooper, Eunice Frishman, Clara Gillis and Fay Eisen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four Schenley High School cheerleaders, including Maxine Cooper, Eunice Frishman, Clara Gillis, and Fay Eisen, standing in row in front of Schenley High School
